# o9ds Component Development

## Constraint

**No third-party UI libraries. No Tailwind. Everything built from scratch.**

- No Ant Design, MUI, Chakra, Radix UI, Headless UI, or any UI component library
- No Tailwind CSS — use plain CSS or custom styles
- No 3rd party styling or component libraries
- Build all components and styles from scratch

## Allowed

- Native HTML elements
- Plain CSS (inline styles, CSS modules, or linked stylesheets)
- Internal design tokens from `index.css` (CSS variables) — no Tailwind
- Internal utility functions / hooks
- Minimal utility libraries (e.g. classnames, date-fns) if approved — **no UI or styling libraries**

## Goal

- Ensure consistency with o9 Design System
- Maintain full control over styling, behavior, and accessibility
- Zero dependency on external UI frameworks or CSS frameworks

## Development Order

1. **Foundations first**: Set design tokens, spacing scale, typography, colors (plain CSS).
2. **Components second**: Build components using native HTML + plain CSS — no libraries.
